item.title: Moparscape is weird
item.dc:creator: @sepheroth243 sepheroth243
item.description:
@sepheroth243 wrote:

The tuts aren’t quite accurate when they point out where your java file is, had this same issue.
What you need to do is go to “my computer”, Then into your “C” drive, then open “program files”, Find a folder that says “java” Open the folder that says “jdk1.5.0 07” then find “javac.exe” if you found that then you should be okay.
If you can’t find it try right clicking in the “bin” folder, arrange icons, and choose “by” name. It’ll be in alphabetical order and it might be easier to find.
This is where my javac.exe is, might be in the same place as yours.
C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_07\bin\javac.exe
Hope this helps
